@node "Intro" "What is it for?"


  OK, what the heck is it?

  It's a replacement for the "CreateNails.ifx" ARexx script
  that comes with ImageFX

  Why?  The original script is quite handy, but it is missing
  some features I wanted, so I wrote a program that has them.

  @{fg shine}FEATURES:@{fg text}

  So, what does it do? 

  (Features with a@{fg shine} * @{fg text}are not available in the original script)

  @{fg fill}1}@{fg shine} * @{fg text}It can start ImageFX for you automatically

  @{fg fill}2}@{fg shine} * @{fg text}It allows you to set default Load and Save paths

  @{fg fill}3}@{fg text} It will create thumbnails for an entire directory

  @{fg fill}4}@{fg text} It can create "remote" thumbnails on your HD for 
     non-writeable volumes (like CD's)

  @{fg fill}5}@{fg text} @{fg shine}*@{fg text} It also reads ALL subdirectories (meaning you can
       even create thumbnails for an entire CD at one time)

  @{fg fill}6}@{fg text} (option) it can be set to skip pictures that already
     have a thumbnail in the target directory

  @{fg fill}7}@{fg text} @{fg shine}*@{fg text} (option) it can create new directories for your
     "remote" thumbnails.  So, if you are scanning a whole CD,
     it won't dump hundreds (maybe thousands) of thumbnails
     in the same directory

  @{fg fill}8}@{fg text} @{fg shine}*@{fg text} (option) it can examine every file found to make sure
     it is really an @{"image file" link "formats" 0} before attempting to load it
     into ImageFX (so you can scan, for example, an entire
     AF CD, and it will find and create thumbnails for every
     picture found.

  @{fg fill}9)@{fg shine} *@{fg text} It corrects a bug found in the Thumbnail loader, the
     Thumbnail browser, and the NailFile.datatype which can
     cause a lock-up or crash with some "remote" thumbnails.     


  @{fg shine}REQUIRES:@{fg text}
  
  ImageFX v 2.00 or newer
  RexxMaster running
  ReqTools  (It will not run otherwise)
@endnode

